<br>
This persons job would be to handle any conflicts that arise within our guild or in relations with others in Norrath.  Say if &quot;Player A&quot; had a problem with &quot;Player B&quot; and they could not resolve it on their own, then they would go to the Magistrate who would act as a moderator and try to come to an agreement with both parties.  If agreement is not reached, then it would be the responsibility of this officer to go to the rest of the officers and bring forth the problem.  Also, if an outside player had a problem with one of our members due to what that player percieves as a infraction against our rules, then it would be the job of the &quot;Magistrate&quot; to investigate the alligations and try to solve the matter.  If the alligations prove true, then this officer would be responsible for bringing it before the high council.  This officer would need to be impartial, value secrecy, and be trustworthy.  I talked to Raloth (jason) about this already and he volunteered for it.  Many may not know him well yet, but I think he would do an excellent job.  It is my sincerest hope that he never has to do anything if he takes on this role, but if this role needs to be filled I am extremely confident in him to handle it with tact and fairness.  Oh yes, Raloth also said he wanted the title to be &quot;Inquisitor&quot; as he feels that the word Magistrate sounds like a, in his own words, &quot;secretary or something.&quot;  *grin*<br>
<br>
